properties.media:imagetext:
The Best and Getting Better!
VANCOUVER
C-GABF
AirBC
At AirBC, we built our reputation by providing
superior service to communities and cities throughout
British Columbia. We've since extended our service
to Seattle and Alberta. Today, AirBC is your Air
Canada Connector, linking Western communities to
Air Canada's world. Across Canada and around the
world.
And beginning June 14th service between
Vancouver - Prince George and
Prince George - Edmonton
Our synchronized schedules permit quick, easy,
convenient connections with Air Canada in
Vancouver, Calgary and Edmonton. To save you
even more time, we offer check-in and seat selection
to Air Canada connecting flights. And through
baggage check-in to your final destination.
As an added reward, every AirBC flight is worth a
minimum of 800 Aeroplan miles. As an added bonus,
from June 14 to July 31, 1987, we are offering an
additional 1000 Aeroplan miles one-way between
Vancouver - Prince George, and Prince George -
Edmonton.
The AirBC fleet consists of six Dash 7's, four Dash
8's and 10 Twin Otters - all designed and built by
DeHavilland Aircraft, a Canadian company which
leads the world in the manufacture of commuter
aircraft. The Dash 8 is one of the world's most
advanced commuter aircraft, cruising at 500 KM per
hour and offering passengers wide body comfort with
full inflight service.
AirBC
Liaison Air Canada Connector
